		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>Attack score mysteries</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>Hi everyone.<br />
<br />
Ive been playing an ogre warrior lately. My RL friend has been playing a dwarf cleric. Last night before we logged off, we sat down and compared numbers like hps/AC with and without buffs to get an idea of exactly what stats we have in certain situations.<br />
<br />
Some strange things happened when we started comparing attack numbers. My friend (the cleric) has an attack score of 238 using his two handed staff. Using the sword that I normally use, I have an attack of about 226. Switching to a hammer (similar stats to my sword) I got an attack of about 175 or something. We considered that maybe two handed weapons get a bonus to attack, so I borrowed my friends staff, and using that I still had an attack of about 225. No matter what I did, my attack never went above 230. We even tried clicking on/off all the different buffs we use at different times and it didnt seem to change anything.<br />
<br />
This seems illogical does it not? Surely an ogre warrior should have a higher attack score than a dwarf cleric?<br />
<br />
Obviously there are other factors to be considered, so here they are. Im level 17 atm, the cleric is level 16. My strength is considerably higher, and my agility is marginally higher. My Hammer and sword skill both read 90/90 while the clerics skill reads 85/85. My &quot;weaponry&quot; skill reads 26/26 while the clerics skill reads 24/24.<br />
<br />
Putting this data togethor, It seems that I should have more bonuses since I seem to have higher stats in everything that should matter. Yet my attack is lower.... in the case of a hammer considerably lower.<br />
<br />
Can anyone explain these observations to me? It just doesnt seem to make sense.<br />
<br />
Why am I so bad at attacking with a hammer?<br />
<br />
Why is a cleric better at attacking than me at all?</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
